# Notes App — Project Documentation

## Overview
This repository contains a small Laravel application (Notes App) with authentication and a simple chat feature. The app uses Laravel for the backend and TailwindCSS/Vite for the frontend assets.

Main features
- User authentication (register, login, logout)
- Notes CRUD (create, read, update, delete) per user
- Simple chat: authenticated users can post messages that are persisted to the database
- Centralized layout and navigation (Blade layout + partial nav)

Tech stack
- PHP 8.2+ / Laravel 12.x
- SQLite (default in .env) — can be switched to MySQL/Postgres in `.env`
- Node.js + npm (for frontend assets / Vite)
- Composer for PHP dependencies

## Quick requirements
- PHP 8.2+
- Composer
- Node.js (LTS) & npm
- SQLite (or other DB configured in `.env`)

## Setup (fresh clone)
1. Copy environment:
   - `cp .env.example .env` (or copy and edit `.env` on Windows)
   - Configure DB in `.env` (by default the project uses sqlite with `database/database.sqlite`).
2. Install PHP dependencies:
   - `composer install`
3. Install JS dependencies and build assets:
   - `npm install`
   - `npm run dev` (development) or `npm run build` (production build)
4. Generate app key and run migrations:
   - `php artisan key:generate`
   - `php artisan migrate`
5. Serve the app locally:
   - `php artisan serve --host=127.0.0.1 --port=8000`

Notes about SQLite: if you use sqlite make sure a database file exists:
```powershell
# from project root
ni .\database\database.sqlite -Force
```

## Local development notes
- Tailwind / Vite assets are in `resources/css` and `resources/js`, entry points are wired via Vite in `resources/js/app.js` and `resources/css/app.css`.
- Blade layouts live in `resources/views/layouts/` and common partials are in `resources/views/partials/`.
  - `resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php` — main app layout (dark theme by default)
  - `resources/views/partials/nav.blade.php` — top navigation included in the layout (Home, Notes, Chat, Login/Register or user name + Logout)

## Routes summary (`routes/web.php`)
- `GET /` — welcome page (public)
- `GET /dashboard` — dashboard (auth + verified)
- Notes (authenticated):
  - `GET /notes` — list notes
  - `POST /notes` — create note
  - `GET /notes/{note}/edit` — edit form
  - `PUT /notes/{note}` — update
  - `DELETE /notes/{note}` — delete
- Chat (authenticated):
  - `GET /chat` — chat page (list messages + send form)
  - `POST /chat/messages` — store message

Authentication routes are loaded via `require __DIR__.'/auth.php';`.

## Where passwords are hashed
- Registration controller hashes passwords before saving: `app/Http/Controllers/Auth/RegisteredUserController.php` uses `Hash::make($request->password)`.
- The `User` model also declares a `password` cast to `'hashed'` in `app/Models/User.php`, which provides an additional safeguard (Eloquent will hash the password on assignment when appropriate).
- For test data, `database/factories/UserFactory.php` creates hashed passwords as well.

## Chat implementation notes
- Model: `app/Models/Message.php` (fields: `id`, `user_id`, `content`, timestamps)
- Migration: `database/migrations/2026_02_22_120000_create_messages_table.php`
- Controller: `app/Http/Controllers/ChatController.php` (methods `index` and `store`)
- Routes: `GET /chat` and `POST /chat/messages` (both in `routes/web.php` under `auth` middleware)
- View: `resources/views/chat/index.blade.php` — extends the main layout and posts messages via a normal HTML form (CSRF-protected). Messages are loaded with `with('user')` to avoid N+1 queries.

## Changed defaults
- Post-login and post-registration redirects were modified to redirect to `/` instead of `/dashboard` by editing the auth controllers:
  - `app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php`
  - `app/Http/Controllers/Auth/RegisteredUserController.php`

## Troubleshooting
- If you see "no such table: messages" when opening `/chat`, make sure migrations were applied: `php artisan migrate`.
- If you see styling issues (invisible text on dark background), check `resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php` and the text color classes (`text-gray-100`, `text-white`, etc.). Clear view cache: `php artisan view:clear`.
- If assets are not loading, rebuild Vite assets: `npm run dev` (or `npm run build`).

